text.tspan: This food truck is okay. Wouldnt say it was the best
pizza I ever had but it was cheap and conviniently
located. Pizza was warm and could tell it wasnt fresh.
The food truck is small so keep your eye out for it.
The menu is simple, prices are very reasonable,
portions were large, food was excellent, and service
I highly recommend for a quick and informal lunch.
Remember to check their Twitter feed before heading
over, and get there early (opening is usually 11:30
AM) to avoid lines. I also paid in cash, which seems
